146
00:08:07,946 --> 00:08:16,079
♪

147
00:08:16,079 --> 00:08:19,040
And I have to tell you,
they were delicious.

148
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:21,167
(crashing boom)

149
00:08:23,294 --> 00:08:24,796
Huh?

150
00:08:24,796 --> 00:08:26,506
(chuckles)

151
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:28,133
Nice work, Agito.

152
00:08:28,133 --> 00:08:30,301
Everything is going
according to my plan.

153
00:08:30,301 --> 00:08:32,303
‐Oh!
‐You big liar!

154
00:08:32,303 --> 00:08:35,432
Now it looks like you two
are the only ones left.

155
00:08:35,432 --> 00:08:36,599
What you gonna do?

156
00:08:36,599 --> 00:08:38,852
I don't think Take
is gonna be much use.

157
00:08:38,852 --> 00:08:42,021
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa...

158
00:08:42,021 --> 00:08:43,481
you mean, you took out Take?

159
00:08:43,481 --> 00:08:46,317
I didn't have to;
he's a piece of crap.

160
00:08:46,317 --> 00:08:47,819
Well, it's no big deal.

161
00:08:47,819 --> 00:08:49,154
It's not like I've been
trying to keep this

162
00:08:49,154 --> 00:08:52,407
a big secret from
everyone or anything.

163
00:08:55,326 --> 00:09:00,457
Take, what have I told you
about having fun behind my back?

164
00:09:00,457 --> 00:09:01,875
Allow me to introduce you.

165
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:05,295
This charming fellow is Take,
the third leader of Trident,

166
00:09:05,295 --> 00:09:07,714
otherwise known as Hatakeyama.

167
00:09:07,714 --> 00:09:09,174
Do you mean that thing?

168
00:09:09,174 --> 00:09:10,383
A computerized superbrain

169
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:11,676
that controls people's
thought waves?

170
00:09:11,676 --> 00:09:13,845
I had no idea their
technology was so advanced!

171
00:09:13,845 --> 00:09:14,929
Get your head outta your ass,

172
00:09:14,929 --> 00:09:17,223
this is nothing but
a crappy old computer.

173
00:09:17,223 --> 00:09:19,684
Come on, you can
see it for yourself.

174
00:09:19,684 --> 00:09:22,687
Come closer, it won't bite.

175
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:24,147
Damn.

176
00:09:24,147 --> 00:09:30,862
♪

177
00:09:30,862 --> 00:09:32,781
It's like a chat room.

178
00:09:32,781 --> 00:09:37,452
♪

179
00:09:37,452 --> 00:09:38,787
Shut the hell up!

180
00:09:38,787 --> 00:09:40,538
I'll kill you,
you son of a bitch!

181
00:09:40,538 --> 00:09:41,748
It's just a monitor, Ikki!

182
00:09:41,748 --> 00:09:43,124
You finally get it.

183
00:09:43,124 --> 00:09:45,418
Hatakeyama isn't the name of
just one member of the team.

184
00:09:45,418 --> 00:09:47,504
All the little idiots
who post these messages

185
00:09:47,504 --> 00:09:50,381
in the chat room are
called Hatakeyama.

186
00:09:50,381 --> 00:09:52,759
So all you have to do is
press a couple of buttons

187
00:09:52,759 --> 00:09:56,387
and you have a pretty good idea
of what the entire team thinks.

188
00:09:56,387 --> 00:09:57,430
Let's have a poll.

189
00:09:57,430 --> 00:10:00,016
Do you accept Ikki Minami
of Kogarasumaru

190
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:03,311
as the new leader of Genesis?

191
00:10:03,311 --> 00:10:05,230
(rapid beeping)

192
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:07,273
Sometimes, these guys
get a little carried away

193
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:09,943
but the bottom line here is that
when they don't have respect

194
00:10:09,943 --> 00:10:12,487
for the man in charge,
then the whole damn show

195
00:10:12,487 --> 00:10:13,947
goes to hell.

196
00:10:13,947 --> 00:10:15,907
In other words,
you're fucked.

197
00:10:15,907 --> 00:10:19,661
♪

198
00:10:19,661 --> 00:10:22,038
Wait, but I was told
that Trident was run

199
00:10:22,038 --> 00:10:23,414
by a council system
where the members

200
00:10:23,414 --> 00:10:25,250
reached their decision
by majority rule.

201
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:28,419
While Hatakeyama is making
its opinion decidedly clear,

202
00:10:28,419 --> 00:10:29,796
what about you?

203
00:10:29,796 --> 00:10:31,131
Benkei?

204
00:10:31,131 --> 00:10:32,674
Yoshitsune?

205
00:10:32,674 --> 00:10:34,175
Before we reach
our final decision,

206
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:36,594
I'd like to hear what
you two have to say.

207
00:10:36,594 --> 00:10:37,720
I have to admit,

208
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:40,014
I'm actually a big fan
of our new leader.

209
00:10:40,014 --> 00:10:41,558
He really impressed
the hell out of me

210
00:10:41,558 --> 00:10:43,768
in that battle
against Behemoth.

211
00:10:43,768 --> 00:10:45,311
But my answer is still no.

212
00:10:45,311 --> 00:10:48,064
If I'm supposed to bow
down and call him boss,

213
00:10:48,064 --> 00:10:50,817
then he's gonna have to prove
to me that he's worth it.

214
00:10:50,817 --> 00:10:53,278
I need to know if that
last win was dumb luck.

215
00:10:53,278 --> 00:10:55,238
My vote is no too.

216
00:10:55,238 --> 00:10:56,948
Hm.

217
00:10:56,948 --> 00:10:59,367
Honestly, I don't give
a damn what you think.

218
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:00,952
If you wanna open
the door and walk out,

219
00:11:00,952 --> 00:11:02,620
well, then that's fine with me.

220
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:05,665
In fact, I'll even escort
you back to your hotel.

221
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:07,625
Shit.

222
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:08,793
But let me warn you.

223
00:11:08,793 --> 00:11:11,045
Everyone in Kansai is
gonna be laughing at you

224
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:13,965
‐for the next hundred years.
‐Whatever; I get it.

225
00:11:13,965 --> 00:11:15,258
Huh?

226
00:11:17,468 --> 00:11:19,637
Ikki!

227
00:11:19,637 --> 00:11:21,598
This is what you want, right?

228
00:11:21,598 --> 00:11:23,808
♪

229
00:11:23,808 --> 00:11:25,143
Thought you'd never ask.

230
00:11:25,143 --> 00:11:27,270
This time, the challenge
will be Kyoto's famous

231
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:28,855
Devil's 30‐30.

232
00:11:28,855 --> 00:11:30,315
What's that?

233
00:11:30,315 --> 00:11:46,664
♪

234
00:11:50,460 --> 00:11:56,633
♪

235
00:11:56,633 --> 00:11:59,969
Normally, 33 wide means
something like 100 meters.

236
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:03,014
But in this case, we're
only doing 33.3 meters.

237
00:12:03,014 --> 00:12:06,476
At any rate, I want you
to jump the entire length.

238
00:12:06,476 --> 00:12:08,561
Think you can handle it...

239
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:10,897
boss?

240
00:12:10,897 --> 00:12:12,774
Is that really a big deal?

241
00:12:12,774 --> 00:12:14,525
I guess it is kinda far to jump.

242
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:17,028
I haven't gotten
to the good part yet.

243
00:12:17,028 --> 00:12:18,863
Members of your team
are gonna line up

244
00:12:18,863 --> 00:12:21,366
and lie on the ground
shoulder‐to‐shoulder.

245
00:12:21,366 --> 00:12:24,327
‐Then you jump over them.
‐That's way too dangerous!

246
00:12:24,327 --> 00:12:25,662
What if he messes up?

247
00:12:25,662 --> 00:12:27,747
Then someone's gonna have
one hell of a headache,

248
00:12:27,747 --> 00:12:29,499
because every one
of those 33 meters

249
00:12:29,499 --> 00:12:31,668
represents one of
your precious friends

250
00:12:31,668 --> 00:12:33,253
putting their life on the line.

251
00:12:33,253 --> 00:12:36,714
The Devil's 30‐30 was created
to resolve team conflicts

252
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:38,049
here in Kyoto.

253
00:12:38,049 --> 00:12:41,219
Kinda like the Parts War.

254
00:12:41,219 --> 00:12:42,553
If you mess it up,

255
00:12:42,553 --> 00:12:45,265
the person you land on
could suffer ruptured organs.

256
00:12:45,265 --> 00:12:47,600
But that's only if
he or she is lucky,

257
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,602
because if you land
on their head,

258
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:51,813
there's gonna be
brains on the pavement.

259
00:12:51,813 --> 00:12:53,398
All right, I'm ready
when you are.

260
00:12:53,398 --> 00:12:56,567
Hold on a sec, don't forget
we're here on our class trip.

261
00:12:56,567 --> 00:12:58,569
They could have the police
searching for us by now.

262
00:12:58,569 --> 00:12:59,988
She's got a good point.

263
00:12:59,988 --> 00:13:02,532
Besides, we can't do the jump
until you have 33 people

264
00:13:02,532 --> 00:13:03,741
to line up.

265
00:13:03,741 --> 00:13:04,951
That's fine.

266
00:13:04,951 --> 00:13:07,370
We'll do it at
2:00 a. m. tomorrow.

267
00:13:07,370 --> 00:13:08,997
If you can manage
to pull this off,

268
00:13:08,997 --> 00:13:12,959
I'll be your follower
for the rest of my life.

269
00:13:12,959 --> 00:13:16,713
(clicking, whirring)

270
00:13:21,467 --> 00:13:24,929
So that's the
Rumble Regalia, huh?

271
00:13:30,184 --> 00:13:44,574
♪

272
00:13:44,574 --> 00:13:46,826
(straining)

273
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:49,620
♪

274
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:52,457
(splashing)

275
00:13:52,457 --> 00:13:55,251
(shouting)

276
00:13:55,251 --> 00:13:57,503
(screaming)

277
00:13:57,503 --> 00:14:07,430
♪

278
00:14:07,430 --> 00:14:09,223
I was wondering what
kind of horrific torture

279
00:14:09,223 --> 00:14:10,850
Orihara had in mind for us,

280
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:12,602
but that wasn't too bad, really.

281
00:14:12,602 --> 00:14:15,438
In that case, I'll give you
some more when we get back.

282
00:14:15,438 --> 00:14:17,732
Enjoy your freedom
while you still can.

283
00:14:17,732 --> 00:14:20,943
♪

284
00:14:20,943 --> 00:14:23,154
(all sigh)

285
00:14:23,154 --> 00:14:25,782
You know, Mr. Orihara was
so worried about you guys,

286
00:14:25,782 --> 00:14:27,909
‐he couldn't even eat.
‐What?

287
00:14:27,909 --> 00:14:29,035
On top of that,

288
00:14:29,035 --> 00:14:30,369
he didn't report you
to the police

289
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:31,662
because he was
afraid he'd ruin

290
00:14:31,662 --> 00:14:33,331
everyone else's class trip.

291
00:14:33,331 --> 00:14:35,416
He said he'd take
full responsibility

292
00:14:35,416 --> 00:14:37,585
and kept waiting.

293
00:14:39,003 --> 00:14:40,421
Yeah, well, Tom‐Tom,
I'm sorry.

294
00:14:40,421 --> 00:14:42,799
Tell that to Mr. Orihara.

295
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:50,473
I know Ikki can make the jump.

296
00:14:50,473 --> 00:14:51,557
It might not be easy,

297
00:14:51,557 --> 00:14:53,434
but he definitely
has what it takes.

298
00:14:53,434 --> 00:14:57,522
I'm more worried about how
he's going to gather 33 people.

299
00:14:57,522 --> 00:14:59,982
(insects chirping)

300
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:04,779
What are you gonna do,
are you really gonna jump?

301
00:15:04,779 --> 00:15:08,199
You said 33.3 meters,
how far is that?

302
00:15:08,199 --> 00:15:09,867
What, like a hundred feet?

303
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:12,120
That doesn't even
sound possible.

304
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:15,289
33.3 meters is a
considerable distance.

305
00:15:15,289 --> 00:15:18,126
My average jump
is only about 32.5.

306
00:15:18,126 --> 00:15:20,044
And given the high pressure
of the situation,

307
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:22,839
it's difficult for riders
to perform their best.

308
00:15:22,839 --> 00:15:24,715
I believe Sora
has the record,

309
00:15:24,715 --> 00:15:28,094
and he only managed 34.2.

310
00:15:28,094 --> 00:15:30,054
In other words, you'll
have to jump a distance

311
00:15:30,054 --> 00:15:33,808
comparable to Sora's old record
without any kind of rehearsal.

312
00:15:33,808 --> 00:15:35,268
You talk too much.

313
00:15:35,268 --> 00:15:37,270
You trying to say I
can't do it, is that it?

314
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:39,063
You don't understand
the situation.

315
00:15:39,063 --> 00:15:41,732
The fate of Genesis
is riding on this jump.

316
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:44,068
Simca has passed the
leadership on to you.

317
00:15:44,068 --> 00:15:46,779
Now you have to prove that
you're worthy to be king.

318
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:48,281
Team Trident is strong.

319
00:15:48,281 --> 00:15:49,574
And unless you're stronger,

320
00:15:49,574 --> 00:15:51,159
then you'll be
seen as a failure.

321
00:15:51,159 --> 00:15:52,869
Genesis would be destroyed,

322
00:15:52,869 --> 00:15:55,746
and that would trigger
battles all over Japan.

323
00:15:55,746 --> 00:15:57,915
Well, then that's
just too bad for them.

324
00:15:57,915 --> 00:16:00,376
This issue here is
whether I can jump or not.

325
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:02,086
And you'll still need 33 people

326
00:16:02,086 --> 00:16:04,755
who aren't afraid of
being crushed to death.

327
00:16:04,755 --> 00:16:05,798
For what it's worth,

328
00:16:05,798 --> 00:16:07,800
we don't mind lying
down for you, Ikki.

329
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:11,804
As long as Kazu's there
with me, I'll be fine.

330
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:14,098
What I mean is‐‐
uh, well, anyway,

331
00:16:14,098 --> 00:16:16,350
I know we don't have
anywhere close to 33 people,

332
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:18,269
but since this whole thing
is so short notice,

333
00:16:18,269 --> 00:16:20,146
they'll just have
to make an exception.

334
00:16:20,146 --> 00:16:22,106
I guess I'll lie down too, Crow.

335
00:16:22,106 --> 00:16:24,066
I mean, what the hell,
I wanna see if your wings

336
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:25,651
are real or not.

337
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:30,448
♪

338
00:16:30,448 --> 00:16:31,657
Hey, you two.

339
00:16:31,657 --> 00:16:33,618
It's seven minutes,
30 seconds till lights out,

340
00:16:33,618 --> 00:16:34,994
so get to bed.

341
00:16:34,994 --> 00:16:37,413
Yes, sir!

342
00:16:37,413 --> 00:16:38,831
Bingo.

343
00:16:38,831 --> 00:16:40,458
(popped top hisses open)

344
00:16:40,458 --> 00:16:41,709
Hm?

345
00:16:41,709 --> 00:16:51,093
♪

346
00:16:51,093 --> 00:16:52,428
Hm.

347
00:16:52,428 --> 00:17:06,651
♪

348
00:17:06,651 --> 00:17:08,986
We've got some breaking
news for you tonight.

349
00:17:08,986 --> 00:17:10,780
Ikki Minami of Kogarasumaru,

350
00:17:10,780 --> 00:17:13,241
otherwise known as the
rookie leader of Genesis,

351
00:17:13,241 --> 00:17:15,993
is going to face off with
Yoshitsune from Trident,

352
00:17:15,993 --> 00:17:19,121
the team that rules
the entire Kansai region.

353
00:17:19,121 --> 00:17:21,249
This is one event
you don't wanna miss.

354
00:17:21,249 --> 00:17:23,668
So I'll see everyone
in Kyoto at 2:00 a. m.

355
00:17:23,668 --> 00:17:27,213
tomorrow morning.

356
00:17:27,213 --> 00:17:30,925
(crowd chatter)

357
00:17:35,388 --> 00:17:43,271
♪

358
00:17:43,271 --> 00:17:45,523
Will I be able
to see the road again?

359
00:17:45,523 --> 00:17:47,567
What if I can't?

360
00:17:47,567 --> 00:17:59,912
♪

361
00:17:59,912 --> 00:18:04,041
‐So how far?
‐24.5; he's not even close.

362
00:18:04,041 --> 00:18:07,795
Hey, what do you
think you're doing?

363
00:18:07,795 --> 00:18:09,130
Ikki?

364
00:18:09,130 --> 00:18:10,381
What's up?

365
00:18:10,381 --> 00:18:12,383
Listen, I just got off
the phone with Mikan

366
00:18:12,383 --> 00:18:13,676
to tell her about tonight,

367
00:18:13,676 --> 00:18:16,429
and it turns out that
everybody knew about it already.

368
00:18:16,429 --> 00:18:17,513
Yeah.

369
00:18:17,513 --> 00:18:19,473
Not only that, Rika's
touring near here,

370
00:18:19,473 --> 00:18:21,559
so she should be coming
to see the match,

371
00:18:21,559 --> 00:18:22,852
and since she'll be here,

372
00:18:22,852 --> 00:18:25,062
Ume and Mikan decided
to come out to show you

373
00:18:25,062 --> 00:18:26,814
‐some support too.
‐Huh?

374
00:18:26,814 --> 00:18:28,733
Don't they have
anything better to do?

375
00:18:28,733 --> 00:18:31,027
They're probably just
coming by to pick on me.

376
00:18:31,027 --> 00:18:34,322
You shouldn't say that, they're
really worried about you.

377
00:18:34,322 --> 00:18:38,492
♪

378
00:18:38,492 --> 00:18:41,203
Because the five of us
are family, aren't we?

379
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:43,497
Right now, I'm sure the only
thing you ever think about

380
00:18:43,497 --> 00:18:45,166
is riding your ATs.

381
00:18:45,166 --> 00:18:47,293
But you know, even if
you don't realize it,

382
00:18:47,293 --> 00:18:50,671
there's lots of people out there
who are worried about you.

383
00:18:50,671 --> 00:18:57,261
♪

384
00:18:57,261 --> 00:19:00,097
You know, it's not too late
to ask Ikki to call it off.

385
00:19:00,097 --> 00:19:01,223
Don't make me laugh.

386
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:02,850
Ikki was the one who
issued the challenge

387
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:04,477
in the first place, remember?

388
00:19:04,477 --> 00:19:06,729
If you were in his shoes,
do you think you could just

389
00:19:06,729 --> 00:19:09,523
turn tail and run after
Yoshitsune brought out

390
00:19:09,523 --> 00:19:12,234
the Rumble Regalia?

391
00:19:12,234 --> 00:19:14,195
That's a good point.

392
00:19:14,195 --> 00:19:15,404
And thanks to the internet,

393
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:19,450
news of the battle has
already spread nationwide.

394
00:19:19,450 --> 00:19:21,118
It's quite impressive, actually.

395
00:19:21,118 --> 00:19:25,456
Riders from all over the
country are coming to watch.

396
00:19:25,456 --> 00:19:29,960
That includes Simca,
but still...

397
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:31,962
‐I was right.
‐Huh?

398
00:19:31,962 --> 00:19:34,173
You act like you're
on Ikki's side,

399
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:35,466
but when it comes down to it,

400
00:19:35,466 --> 00:19:38,969
you don't have an ounce
of faith in him, do you?

401
00:19:38,969 --> 00:19:41,138
But more importantly,
if we wanna win this,

402
00:19:41,138 --> 00:19:43,265
there's something
I need from you.

403
00:19:43,265 --> 00:19:45,810
(chanted)
Crush him, crush him!

404
00:19:51,148 --> 00:19:52,316
Good evening, everyone.

405
00:19:52,316 --> 00:19:54,860
Tonight, we're coming
to you live from Kyoto.

406
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:56,320
Hold on tight, because
we're bringing you

407
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:58,030
the battle of the century,

408
00:19:58,030 --> 00:20:00,241
Kogarasumaru versus Trident.

409
00:20:00,241 --> 00:20:02,535
This battle is being
broadcast worldwide,

410
00:20:02,535 --> 00:20:03,994
so I'd like to give
a special hello

411
00:20:03,994 --> 00:20:06,747
to all the Storm Riders watching
from out of the country.

412
00:20:06,747 --> 00:20:09,083
Tonight, we're gonna show you
how we do it in Kyoto

413
00:20:09,083 --> 00:20:10,918
with the Devil's 30‐30.

414
00:20:10,918 --> 00:20:12,878
You're about to see
history in the making,

415
00:20:12,878 --> 00:20:14,839
so don't go away.

416
00:20:14,839 --> 00:20:17,383
(chanted)
Crush him, crush him!

417
00:20:22,513 --> 00:20:24,807
This crowd is really
getting on my nerves.

418
00:20:24,807 --> 00:20:26,684
Why is everyone so rude?

419
00:20:26,684 --> 00:20:28,144
They're just rooting
for the home team.

420
00:20:28,144 --> 00:20:29,937
Where the hell is
that dumbass, anyway?

421
00:20:29,937 --> 00:20:32,523
Ten bucks say he wussed out.

422
00:20:35,526 --> 00:20:37,695
If we don't hurry, we're
not gonna make it in time.

423
00:20:37,695 --> 00:20:39,947
It's not our fault
Orihara put booby traps

424
00:20:39,947 --> 00:20:42,324
‐all over the hotel.
‐Huh?

425
00:20:42,324 --> 00:20:45,035
♪

426
00:20:45,035 --> 00:20:47,371
Hey, wait a second, what
are you guys doing here?

427
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:49,665
You should be back at the
hotel, pretending to be us.

428
00:20:49,665 --> 00:20:52,752
I know, but you need 33 people
for the jump, don'tcha?

429
00:20:52,752 --> 00:20:53,961
(gasp)

430
00:20:53,961 --> 00:20:55,254
All of us decided
on this together.

431
00:20:55,254 --> 00:20:56,714
I know it sounds kinda cheesy,

432
00:20:56,714 --> 00:21:00,259
but we're all really proud to
have you represent our school.

433
00:21:00,259 --> 00:21:01,844
If you're gonna stake
your life on a battle,

434
00:21:01,844 --> 00:21:04,638
then the least we can do
is come here to support you.

435
00:21:04,638 --> 00:21:07,183
♪

436
00:21:07,183 --> 00:21:09,602
You guys could get
killed, you know.

437
00:21:09,602 --> 00:21:11,645
(murmured assent)

438
00:21:11,645 --> 00:21:12,938
♪

439
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:15,941
Well, okay, I'll try not
to aim for your head.

440
00:21:15,941 --> 00:21:18,944
♪

441
00:21:18,944 --> 00:21:20,446
Be careful!

442
00:21:20,446 --> 00:21:27,411
♪

443
00:21:27,411 --> 00:21:31,123
(crowd cheering)

444
00:21:31,123 --> 00:21:34,376
It looks like Ikki Minami
has finally made his appearance.

445
00:21:34,376 --> 00:21:35,795
Now, without further ado,

446
00:21:35,795 --> 00:21:37,630
let's get this show on the road!

447
00:21:37,630 --> 00:21:41,258
This is the moment
we've all been waiting for.

448
00:21:41,258 --> 00:21:43,719
(crowd cheering)

449
00:21:49,099 --> 00:23:42,546
♪

450
00:23:45,674 --> 00:23:48,969
♪

451
00:23:48,969 --> 00:23:50,429
All right, here I go.

452
00:23:50,429 --> 00:23:51,555
I'm gonna jump!

453
00:23:51,555 --> 00:23:53,682
Yoshitsune's gonna be
sorry he challenged me.

454
00:23:53,682 --> 00:23:55,935
You can do it, Ikki,
I just know it.

455
00:23:55,935 --> 00:23:57,311
I believe in you.

456
00:23:57,311 --> 00:24:00,940
Because, well, you've always
been my number one hero.

457
00:24:00,940 --> 00:24:02,566
Thanks, Ringo, don't worry.

458
00:24:02,566 --> 00:24:04,485
I won't let you
down, just watch!

459
00:24:04,485 --> 00:24:06,153
I'm going to
the top of the sky!

460
00:24:06,153 --> 00:24:08,989
Next time on Air Gear,
the final episode!

461
00:24:08,989 --> 00:24:12,034
‐I'm a genius!
‐Yeah, not so much.

